14 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Nonprofit hospital reporting requirements -- rulemaking authority.
15 Each nonprofit hospital shall report its charity care and community benefit spending to the department of public
16 health and human services in a THE manner provided FOR IN 50-5-106 AND by the department by rule. The report
17 must include the following information related to the financial assistance and other community benefits
18 spending the nonprofit hospital reported on schedule H of internal revenue service form 990 for the most recent
19 tax year:
20 (1) the net community benefit expense the nonprofit hospital reported for community health
21 improvement services and community benefit operations and for community building activities and how the
22 expenses related to the needs identified in the most recent community health needs assessment the nonprofit
23 hospital conducted as required under 26 U.S.C. 501(r)(3); and
24 (2) for expenses reported in the financial assistance at cost, other means-tested government
25 programs, subsidized health services, and bad debt categories:
26 (a) the net community benefit expense amount reported on schedule H for financial assistance,
27 other means-tested government programs, and subsidized health services;
28 (b) the total amount the nonprofit hospital reported for bad debt expenses; and
